// Boat-permit question bank — GIFT export for Moodle.
// Self-contained: figures are embedded as base64 data URIs.

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Signalisation des voies et des bateaux

::q-fr-cevni-47-fc5e54b6:: [html]On an inland waterway, what does ONE prolonged blast from a vessel generally mean? {
=“Attention”
~“I am turning around”
~“I am stopped”
####[html]One prolonged blast is the “Attention” signal; it draws other vessels' attention.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://unece.org/transport/inland-water-transport">CEVNI — signal général « Attention » (un son prolongé) — CEVNI — Code européen des voies de navigation intérieure (CEE-ONU, Résolution n° 24)</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Réglementation, permis et radio

::q-fr-codetransports-58-ce87c1b3:: [html]Driving a boat under the influence of alcohol is\: {
=Prohibited
~Allowed on canals
~Tolerated at night
####[html]Prohibited\: the skipper must be fit to steer and react, as when driving a vehicle.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/texte_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/">Code des transports, art. L.4274-14 — conduite en état alcoolique (≥ 0,5 g/L) — Code des transports — navigation intérieure (titre de navigation, alcoolémie, règlements particuliers de police)</a>
}

::q-fr-codetransports-76-9ac86898:: [html]Which document, specific to the boat, must be available aboard on inland waters? {
=The boat's circulation card
~A road map of the area
~Only the engine manual
####[html]The boat's circulation card (navigation title), together with, where applicable, the driver's licence and proof of insurance.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/texte_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/">Code des transports, art. L.4221-1 — titre de navigation (carte de circulation) — Code des transports — navigation intérieure (titre de navigation, alcoolémie, règlements particuliers de police)</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Protection de l'environnement

::q-fr-codetransports-78-6de9f8e6:: [html]What should the boater do with waste water (black water) on inland waters? {
=Hold it in a tank and empty it ashore
~Discharge it discreetly at night
~Discharge it far from the banks
####[html]Keep it in a holding tank aboard, then empty it at shore collection facilities; discharging it into the waterway is prohibited.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/texte_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/">Code des transports, art. R.4241-63 / CDNI (décret 2010-197) — eaux usées (cuve, dépôt à terre) — Code des transports — navigation intérieure (titre de navigation, alcoolémie, règlements particuliers de police)</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Réglementation, permis et radio

::q-fr-decret2007-56-ff63a4eb:: [html]What licence is needed to drive a motor pleasure boat over 4.5 kW on rivers and canals? {
=The permis plaisance inland-waters option
~No licence is needed
~The côtière option always suffices
####[html]The permis plaisance “eaux intérieures” option (the côtière option is for the sea).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/loda/id/JORFTEXT000000648362/">Décret n° 2007-1167 du 2 août 2007, art. 2 — option eaux intérieures — Décret n° 2007-1167 du 2 août 2007 relatif au permis de conduire des bateaux de plaisance à moteur</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Sécurité et matériel d'armement

::q-fr-division245-53-87ddd9c0:: [html]Aboard a small craft on inland waters, what must each person have? {
=A personal flotation device
~A compulsory drysuit
~Nothing, if they can swim
####[html]Every person aboard must have a suitable personal flotation device (lifejacket / buoyancy aid).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/loda/id/JORFTEXT000032036538/">Arrêté du 10 février 2016 (Division 245), art. 5 — EIF par personne (eaux intérieures) — Division 245 (arrêté du 10 février 2016) — matériel d'armement et de sécurité des bateaux de plaisance en eaux intérieures</a>
}

::q-fr-division245-74-61c84140:: [html]Among the useful equipment aboard a small craft, you must have a means of\: {
=Bailing the boat out (scoop or pump)
~Measuring the channel depth
~Recharging the VHF
####[html]Bailing the boat out (scoop, pump or bucket) if water comes in, in addition to the personal flotation devices.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/loda/id/JORFTEXT000032036538/">Arrêté du 10 février 2016 (Division 245), art. 5 — dispositif d'assèchement — Division 245 (arrêté du 10 février 2016) — matériel d'armement et de sécurité des bateaux de plaisance en eaux intérieures</a>
}

::q-fr-division245-75-641fbe2b:: [html]To be able to stop safely away from a quay, a craft must have\: {
=An anchor with its rode
~A second engine
~A liferaft
####[html]A suitable means of anchoring (an anchor with its line) to hold the boat.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/loda/id/JORFTEXT000032036538/">Arrêté du 10 février 2016 (Division 245), art. 6 — ligne de mouillage — Division 245 (arrêté du 10 février 2016) — matériel d'armement et de sécurité des bateaux de plaisance en eaux intérieures</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Réglementation, permis et radio

::q-fr-iturr-77-446e0b94:: [html]To use a VHF radio aboard, the skipper must, as a rule, hold\: {
=The restricted radiotelephone certificate (CRR)
~The boat licence alone
~No particular certificate
####[html]The restricted radiotelephone certificate (CRR), which authorises the use of a VHF. Since 2011 it is no longer required in French territorial waters for a hand-held VHF without DSC; it remains required for a fixed or DSC-equipped VHF and for navigating abroad.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.itu.int/pub/R-REG-RR">UIT, Règlement des radiocommunications, art. 47 — certificat d'opérateur (CRR, délivré par l'ANFR) — UIT — Règlement des radiocommunications (canaux VHF maritimes, procédures de détresse et d'urgence)</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Voies navigables et stationnement

::q-fr-rgp-40-d508050f:: [html]Under the inland navigation police regulation (RGP), what is a “small craft” (menue embarcation)? {
=A vessel under 20 metres
~Any vessel under 24 metres
~A vessel under 15 metres only
####[html]As a rule, a vessel with a hull length under 20 metres (excluding passenger vessels, tugs, etc.).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP (Code des transports, art. R.4000-2, 7°) — menue embarcation (< 20 m) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-41-9ea04935:: [html]Where is mooring (stopping) of a vessel generally prohibited on a waterway? {
=Under bridges and in narrow passages
~Along every fitted quay
~Nowhere — mooring is unrestricted
####[html]Mooring is forbidden where it hampers navigation (under bridges, in narrow passages) and wherever a sign prohibits it.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-54-2 — stationnement interdit (ponts, passages étroits) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-42-1f794b0d:: [html]To limit wash (the wake that erodes banks and rocks moored boats), what must the driver do near the banks? {
=Reduce speed
~Increase speed to pass quickly
~Hug the bank as close as possible
####[html]Reduce speed when approaching banks, harbours and moored boats, to limit the wash.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-21 — vitesse et batillage — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Écluses, barrages et ouvrages

::q-fr-rgp-43-e53f0eaf:: [html]At a lock entrance, what does a RED light mean? {
=Entry forbidden, you must wait
~Entry authorised
~Exit from the lock only
####[html]A single red light means “no entry”; wait. A green light authorises entry; two red lights mean the lock is out of service.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-31 §1 — feux d'écluse (rouge \= accès interdit) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-44-9193cab9:: [html]Which light authorises entry into a lock? {
=The green light
~The red light
~Two red lights
####[html]A green light authorises entry. Two red lights mean the lock is out of service.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-31 §1 — feu vert d'écluse (accès autorisé) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-45-45186bd5:: [html]In a lock chamber, how should you handle your lines during locking? {
=Tend and adjust them, never made fast to a fixed point
~Make them fast hard to a fixed cleat
~Remove all the lines
####[html]The water level changes\: tend the lines and pay out or take in as needed, never make them fast to a fixed point (risk of parting or listing).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-30/-31 — conduite dans le sas d'écluse — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Signalisation des voies et des bateaux

::q-fr-rgp-46-7ffa546c:: [html]On a waterway, what does a rectangular sign with a red border and a white horizontal bar mean? {
=No passage / no entry
~Obligation to stop and refuel
~Recommendation to slow down
####[html]It is a prohibition sign (type A.1)\: no entry / passage forbidden.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, panneau A.1 — interdiction de passer — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-48-43e11fe7:: [html]At night, a power-driven vessel underway on inland waters shows a light to port. What colour is it? {
=Red
~Green
~Yellow
####[html]As at sea\: port sidelight red, starboard green, plus a white masthead light and a sternlight.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-48-12 — feux des menues embarcations (bâbord rouge) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-49-92709847:: [html]At night, a vessel moored away from the bank, outside a harbour, most often shows\: {
=An all-round white light
~A flashing red light
~No light
####[html]An ordinary white light visible all round, to signal its presence to other vessels.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-48-20 — signalisation en stationnement (feu blanc) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Règles de barre et de route

::q-fr-rgp-50-30f74d5c:: [html]On inland waters, with respect to large vessels, ferries and vessels on a regular service, small craft (pleasure boats) must\: {
=Keep out of their way
~Hold their course, having priority
~Force them to stop
####[html]Small craft must leave the way clear for large vessels, ferries and convoys\: they keep out of their way.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-3 — menues embarcations s'écartent des grands bateaux et bacs — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-51-397ff43c:: [html]As a general rule on an inland waterway, to which side should a vessel keep? {
=To its right (starboard)
~To its left (port)
~In the middle of the channel
####[html]Each vessel keeps to its right (starboard) as a rule; vessels then pass port to port, unless signs indicate otherwise.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-6 §1 — venir sur tribord (croisement bâbord-bâbord) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-52-5f6a7405:: [html]In a narrow passage (under a bridge, a tight channel) where crossing is impossible, what must the driver do? {
=Make sure the passage is clear before entering
~Always enter first
~Speed up to force through
####[html]Make sure the passage is clear before entering and give way per the signs; on rivers priority goes to the down-bound vessel (going with the current).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-8 — passage étroit (priorité à l'avalant) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Sécurité et matériel d'armement

::q-fr-rgp-54-03dfc925:: [html]A vessel's identification mark (registration) must be\: {
=Displayed visibly and legibly on the hull
~Kept only in the boat's papers
~Optional for pleasure craft
####[html]It must be displayed visibly and legibly on the hull, so the vessel can be identified.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-47-1 — marque d'identification du bateau — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-55-1942c7d7:: [html]Before getting under way, what must the skipper check (duty of care)? {
=The boat's condition, the safety gear and the weather
~Only the fuel level
~Nothing — checks are the lock's job
####[html]Ensure the boat and engine are sound, the safety equipment is aboard, and the conditions (water level, weather) are suitable.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. R.4241-9/-10 — devoir général de prudence du conducteur — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Réglementation, permis et radio

::q-fr-rgp-57-acb1b55b:: [html]Besides the general police regulation (RGP), a particular waterway may also be governed by\: {
=A particular police regulation (RPP)
~The road traffic code alone
~No other rule
####[html]A particular police regulation (RPP) adapts the general rules to the local circumstances of a given waterway or reach.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">Code des transports, art. R.4241-31/-32 — règlement particulier de police (RPP) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Protection de l'environnement

::q-fr-rgp-59-32f112e9:: [html]On inland waters, discharging hydrocarbons, waste water or rubbish into the waterway is\: {
=Prohibited
~Allowed in small amounts
~Free outside harbours
####[html]Prohibited\: such discharges pollute the waterway and must be collected and disposed of in the proper facilities.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP (Code des transports, art. R.4241-62) — rejet d'hydrocarbures interdit — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-60-80fd925f:: [html]To limit bank erosion and disturbance to wildlife, the boater should above all\: {
=Reduce speed and wash near the banks
~Run at full speed in the centre
~Moor in the reed beds
####[html]Reduce speed and wash when approaching banks, reed beds and sensitive natural areas.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-21 — réduire vitesse et batillage près des berges — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Voies navigables et stationnement

::q-fr-rgp-61-0b480791:: [html]On inland waters, what is a “down-bound” (avalant) vessel? {
=A vessel going downstream
~A vessel going upstream
~A vessel stopped against the bank
####[html]A down-bound vessel goes with the current (downstream); an up-bound (montant) one goes against it. On rivers the down-bound vessel, less manoeuvrable, has priority.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-1 et -53-6 §2 — montant/avalant (priorité à l'avalant) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-62-3e9f3647:: [html]Along a river or canal, how is your position located? {
=By kilometre points (bank markers)
~By latitude and longitude alone
~By nautical miles
####[html]By kilometre points (PK), shown by markers or plates on the banks, counting the kilometres from the start of the waterway.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">Voie navigable — repérage par points kilométriques (PK) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-63-17514081:: [html]Before passing under a bridge or a power line, what must the driver check? {
=That the air draft is less than the available headroom
~That its speed is at maximum
~That its anchor is down
####[html]That the air draft (the boat's height above the water) is less than the available headroom, shown by the signs.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, panneau C.2 — hauteur libre limitée (tirant d'air) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Écluses, barrages et ouvrages

::q-fr-rgp-64-3d9c8ad0:: [html]At a lock, who sets the order and manner in which vessels enter? {
=The lock-keeper and the lock's signs
~The fastest vessel
~Each driver, freely
####[html]The lock-keeper (or the lock's signs / automatic system); follow their instructions and the lights.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-31 §4 et §12 — instructions de l'éclusier — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-65-223fd27d:: [html]At a lock, what do TWO red lights mean? {
=The lock is out of service
~Entry is immediately authorised
~Exit is compulsory
####[html]The lock is out of service / closed to navigation. A single red light means “wait”, and a green light authorises entry.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-31 §1(a) — deux feux rouges (écluse hors service) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Signalisation des voies et des bateaux

::q-fr-rgp-66-ae886700:: [html]On inland waters, how do you recognise a PROHIBITION sign? {
=By its red border
~By being entirely blue
~By a green triangular shape
####[html]Prohibition signs have a red border (often a white bar with red), like the “no entry” sign.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, section A — signaux d'interdiction (bord rouge) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-67-51ebf59c:: [html]What does a rectangular BLUE sign with a white symbol generally give? {
=Information / guidance
~An absolute prohibition
~An immediate danger
####[html]Blue rectangular signs give information (mooring allowed, ferry, service point, etc.).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, section E — signaux d'indication (bleus) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-68-e7601837:: [html]A square BLUE sign bearing a white letter “P” means\: {
=Mooring permitted
~Mooring prohibited
~Marina 1 km ahead
####[html]Mooring (berthing) is permitted at this spot.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, panneau E.5 — stationnement autorisé (P) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-69-a7ece36b:: [html]A red-bordered sign bearing a white arrow indicates\: {
=An obligation to follow the shown direction
~A mere recommendation
~A bathing area
####[html]It is a mandatory sign\: you must follow the direction (the side) shown by the arrow.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, panneau B.1 — obligation (suivre la flèche) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-70-c06c8fc1:: [html]A sign bearing a number (e.g. “3.50 m”) generally indicates\: {
=A limit on headroom, width or depth
~The distance to the next lock
~The waterway's number
####[html]A restriction\: for example the available headroom, width or depth (series C signs). A maximum speed is instead a mandatory sign (B.6).<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, annexe 5, section C — restriction (hauteur, largeur ou profondeur) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Règles de barre et de route

::q-fr-rgp-71-6fe61170:: [html]On a flowing river, when an up-bound and a down-bound vessel meet, which has priority? {
=The down-bound vessel
~The up-bound vessel
~The larger of the two vessels
####[html]The down-bound vessel (going with the current) has priority because it manoeuvres less easily; the up-bound vessel leaves it the way and the chosen side.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-6 §2 — priorité de l'avalant — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-72-c619375a:: [html]On still water, two power-driven vessels meet head-on. What do they do? {
=Each alters to starboard
~Each alters to port
~They both stop
####[html]Each alters to starboard (its right) so they pass port to port.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-6 §1 — rencontre (chacun sur tribord) — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

::q-fr-rgp-73-dc2077e7:: [html]On inland waters, on which side does a vessel normally overtake another? {
=On the port (left) side of the overtaken vessel
~Always on the starboard side
~By passing very close to it
####[html]As a rule on the port (left) side of the vessel being overtaken, once sure the manoeuvre is safe; the overtaking vessel keeps clear of the one overtaken.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP, art. A.4241-53-11 §1 — dépassement par bâbord — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}

$CATEGORY: Boat permit · Lake Geneva (EN)/Protection de l'environnement

::q-fr-rgp-79-0edde366:: [html]When refuelling, what precaution prevents water pollution? {
=Avoid any overflow (do not fill to the brim)
~Fill as fast as possible
~Rinse the tank with canal water
####[html]Refuel unhurriedly and do not fill to the brim (use a funnel, watch the level) to avoid any fuel spilling into the water.<br>Source \: <a href\="https\://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/codes/section_lc/LEGITEXT000023086525/LEGISCTA000027232795/">RGP (Code des transports, art. R.4241-62) — prévention de la pollution — Règlement général de police de la navigation intérieure (RGP/RGPNI) — Code des transports, art. R. 4241-1 et s.</a>
}
